## Controversies and Criticisms

While Rockefeller's contributions were substantial, his legacy is complex due to the following:

- **Monopolistic Practices:** His aggressive business tactics led to the breakup of Standard Oil by the U.S. Supreme Court in 1911 for violating antitrust laws ([History.com, 2020](https://www.history.com/topics/early-20th-century-us/john-d-rockefeller)).
- **Labor Relations:** Though he treated top managers well, some accounts suggest that workers faced exploitation and poor conditions, leading to criticism of his "Robber Baron" reputation ([Prezi.com, 2018](https://prezi.com/sgdfcqut-_db/what-positive-and-negative-impact-did-john-d-rockefeller-ha/)).
- **Public Perception:** Rockefeller was simultaneously viewed as a "great man" and an industrial statesman by supporters, and as a villain and monopolist by detractors.

Despite these criticisms, many historians acknowledge that his contributions to economic development and philanthropy had a net positive effect on American society ([Bartleby.com, 2020](https://www.bartleby.com/essay/John-D-Rockefeller-a-Positive-Influence-on-PKCNWQPCTC)).

